HEADWORD: Mantrap
<hw>Man"trap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A trap
for catching trespassers.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dangerous place, as an open hatch, into which one
may fall.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mantua</ent>⟦br⟧
